@startuml seq_19_manage_drafts
title Sequence Diagram: UC-19 Manage Drafts

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Draft Controller" as Controller
participant "Draft Service" as Service
participant "Draft Repo" as DraftRepo
participant "Post Service" as PostService

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open Drafts
Frontend -> Controller: (1.2) GET /api/drafts
Controller -> Service: (2.1) Load user's draft list
Service -> DraftRepo: (2.2) Find drafts by user ID
DraftRepo --> Service: (2.3) List of drafts
Service --> Controller: (3.1) Drafts data
Controller --> Frontend: (3.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (3.3) Display drafts

User -> Frontend: (4.1) Create or edit a draft
User -> Frontend: (5.1) Save the draft
Frontend -> Controller: (5.2) PUT /api/drafts/{id} {draft_data}
Controller -> Service: (6.1) Save draft request
Service -> DraftRepo: (6.2) Validate ownership and draft content
Service -> DraftRepo: (7.1) Store draft changes
DraftRepo --> Service: (7.2) Draft updated
Service --> Controller: (11.1) Updated draft state
Controller --> Frontend: (11.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (11.3) Show "Saved" indicator

User -> Frontend: (8.1) Publish draft
Frontend -> Controller: (8.2) POST /api/drafts/{id}/publish
Controller -> Service: (8.3) Publish draft request
Service -> DraftRepo: (8.4) Load draft content
DraftRepo --> Service: (8.5) Draft data
Service -> PostService: (8.6) Create post from draft
PostService --> Service: (8.7) Post created (postID)
Service -> DraftRepo: (9.1) Delete draft after publishing
DraftRepo --> Service: (9.2) Draft deleted
Service --> Controller: (11.4) Updated draft state
Controller --> Frontend: (11.5) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (11.6) Redirect to newly published post
@enduml
